The chemical formula for table salt is NaCl. Table salt, commonly used for seasoning and preserving food, is composed of sodium (Na) and chlorine (Cl) atoms chemically bonded together. In chemical notation, the formula NaCl represents one atom of sodium combined with one atom of chlorine. This ionic compound is known for its crystalline structure and distinctive taste. The formula NaCl helps chemists and students identify the substance quickly and understand its basic chemical composition. When studying compounds, formulas like NaCl provide essential information about the elements involved and their ratios. This knowledge is foundational for anyone exploring chemistry, cooking, or even everyday substances.
